com.hidglobal.biosdk

Interface BioSDKDevice


  • public interface BioSDKDevice
    The Bio SDK Device interface. Provides methods to interact with the biometric device.

    • Method Detail

      • capture_async

        BioDeviceStatus capture_async(int nTimeout,
                              ICaptureListener listener)
        Initiates a fingerprint capture. Asynchronous mode. visitor callback shall receive results of the capture.
        Parameters:
        nTimeout - timeout, in seconds, of when the command exits if fingerprint impression not detected.
        listener - the listener
        Returns:
        the bio device status

      • verify_async

        BioDeviceStatus verify_async(List<byte[]> templateList,
                             int nTimeoutSeconds,
                             IVerifyListener listener)
        Verifies one or more fingerprint templates against an active capture. Asynchronous version. visitor callback shall receive results of the verification.
        Parameters:
        templateList - a Java List of one or more templates to verify against. Max: 3 templates.
        nTimeoutSeconds - timeout, in seconds, of when the command exits if fingerprint impression not detected.
        listener - the listener
        Returns:
        the bio device status

      • waitForFingerClear_asynch

        BioDeviceStatus waitForFingerClear_asynch(int nTimeOutSeconds,
                                          IWaitForFingerClearListener listener)
        Waits for finger to be removed from the device. visitor callback shall receive result status.
        Parameters:
        nTimeOutSeconds - timeout, in seconds, of when the command exits if fingerprint impression not detected.
        listener - the listener
        Returns:
        the bio device status

      • capture

        BioDeviceStatus capture(int timeoutSeconds,
                        IStatusListener listener)
        Capture bio device status. visitor callback should return true. Return false to cancel capture.
        Parameters:
        timeoutSeconds - timeout, in seconds, of when the command exits if fingerprint impression not detected.
        listener - the listener
        Returns:
        the bio device status

      • verify

        BioDeviceStatus verify(int timeoutSeconds,
                       List<byte[]> templateList,
                       IStatusListener listener)
        Verifies one or more fingerprint templates against an active capture. visitor callback should return true. Return false to cancel verification.
        Parameters:
        templateList - a list of one or more templates to verify against. Limit is 3 templates.
        Returns:
        the bio device status

      • waitForFingerClear

        BioDeviceStatus waitForFingerClear(int nTimeoutSeconds,
                                   IStatusListener listener)
        Waits for finger to be removed from the device. visitor callback should return true. Return false to cancel wait for finger clear.
        Parameters:
        nTimeoutSeconds - the n timeout seconds
        Returns:
        the bio device status

      • setConfigurationState

        BioDeviceStatus setConfigurationState(Map<String,String> obj)
        Sets configuration state. Can set one or more configurations in string map parameter.

        Supported Configurations and Valid Values:
        trigger_timeout
        In seconds. Positive integer 0 to 65535. 0 = infinite (no timeout).

        trigger_override
        0 = presence detection on (default). 1 = presence detection off (sensor captures image immediately).

        matching_security_level
        CONVENIENCE
        MEDIUM
        MEDIUM_HIGH
        HIGH

        padSecurityLevel
        CONVENIENCE
        MEDIUM
        HIGH
        Parameters:
        obj - configuration map
        Returns:
        the bio device status

      • getLastPADResult

        int getLastPADResult()
        Gets last PAD result (Presentation Attack Detection).
        Returns:
